# Symphony AI Server — Cline Rules
# Migrated from .cursor/rules/*.mdc

## What This Project Is

AI backend for **Symphony Smart Homes** (Denver, CO residential AV/smart-home). Owner: Matt Earley.

### Repository Contents
- **OpenClaw** — orchestrator running every 5 min (email analysis, job management, follow-ups, notifications, trading)
- **Bob the Conductor** — AI voice receptionist (Twilio + OpenAI Realtime API)
- **Client Portal** — per-client status page with native e-signature (port 8096)
- **Polymarket Bot** — prediction market trading ($402 portfolio, weather category focus)
- **Email Monitor** — Zoho IMAP polling, SQLite dedup, read/replied/new tracking
- **Notification Hub** — iMessage routing, high-priority-only alerts
- **Mission Control** — single-page deployment dashboard
- **X-Intake** — Twitter/X link analysis and video transcription pipeline

### Tech Stack
| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Runtime | Docker Compose, 19 containers on Mac Mini M4 ("Bob") |
| Voice | Node.js, Twilio Media Streams, OpenAI Realtime API |
| AI/LLM | OpenAI API (GPT-4o, Whisper), Ollama (qwen3:8b local) |
| Database | SQLite (decision_journal.db, jobs.db, follow_ups.db, emails.db) |
| Messaging | Redis (auth required: password d19c9b0faebeee9927555eb8d6b28ec9) |
| Infrastructure | Docker, Tailscale VPN, Mac Mini M4 |
| Frontend | Vanilla JS/HTML/CSS (no frameworks) |

### Coding Standards
- **Python**: PEP 8, type hints where practical, docstrings on public functions
- **JavaScript**: 'use strict', CommonJS, 2-space indent, single quotes
- **Shell scripts**: set -euo pipefail, comment every non-obvious step
- **No TypeScript, no React/Vue** — plain JS only
- **No interactive editors** — never use vim, nano, or crontab -e. One-liner commands only.

### Git Rules
- ALWAYS use `bash scripts/pull.sh` instead of bare `git pull`
- Commit messages: imperative mood, 72 chars max subject
- Never commit .env files, API keys, or SQLite databases
- The pull script auto-detects and fixes merge conflict markers

### Docker Patterns
- OpenClaw code is bind-mounted (./openclaw:/app) — Python-only edits just need `docker restart openclaw`
- Full rebuilds: `docker compose up -d --build <service>`
- Ship script: `./scripts/symphony-ship.sh` (build, up, verify)
- All containers connect to Redis with auth URL: `redis://:d19c9b0faebeee9927555eb8d6b28ec9@redis:6379`

### Key Paths on Bob
| Path | Contents |
|---|---|
| ~/AI-Server/ | This repo |
| ~/AI-Server/.env | All secrets (OpenAI, Zoho, Kraken, ACH, etc.) |
| ~/AI-Server/data/openclaw/ | SQLite DBs (jobs.db, decision_journal.db, follow_ups.db) |
| ~/AI-Server/data/transcripts/ | X video transcripts by author |
| ~/Dropbox/[Project]/Client/ | Shared client files |
| ~/Dropbox/[Project]/Internal/ | Internal work (never shared) |
| ~/Dropbox/[Project]/Archive/ | Old versions |
| /tmp/imessage-bridge.log | iMessage bridge logs |

### Security Rules
- All API keys via environment variables — never hardcoded
- Version numbers are internal only — client-facing docs use "updated proposal"
- Each client document needs its own separate Dropbox share link
- ACH details (routing/account) are not sensitive — they appear on every invoice

